canonical:
  title: 枯木
  author: 李湛
  language: lzh
  text: 白虯倒立碧山陰斤斧人遙歲月深堪嘆春風吹又過舊枝無復有花心
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 枯木
  author: 李湛
  language: lzh
  text: 白虯倒立碧山陰。斤斧人遙歲月深。堪嘆春風吹又過。舊枝無復有花心。
korean:
  title: 고목
  author: 이담
  language: kor
  text: |-
    흰 이무기 푸른 산 그늘에 거꾸로 서 있는데
    자귀와 도끼를 가진 사람 멀어졌고 오랫동안 세월도 깊어졌다
    못내 한탄하노니 봄바람이 또 불어 지나가건만
    옛 가지에 다시는 꽃 필 마음이 없네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_1050&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Dead Wood
  author: Lee Dam
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A white serpent stands inverted in the blue mountain's shadow.
    The woodcutter's axe grows distant, the years pile deep.
    I lament—spring wind blows and passes once more,
    yet the ancient branches harbor no heart to bloom again.
  footnotes:
    - The 'white serpent' (白虯) is an image of a weathered, pale tree trunk standing bare against the mountainside. In classical poetry, such images often evoke both the beauty of decay and the melancholy of transience.
    - The poem uses the woodcutter's absence as a marker of time's passage, suggesting that even potential use or purpose has become distant and forgotten.
